Gage Skidmore/FlickrOne of the biggest stories coming out of the 2018 midterms was about the election fraud that occurred in North Carolina.
But leave it up to Majority Leader Mitch McConnell to blame it all on Democrats.
On Senate floor, @senatemajldr McConnell shamelessly blames Dems for Mark Harris' election fraud in North Carolina, because Dems haven't supported voter ID laws.
pic.twitter.com/PGZw23p4PU — Aaron Rupar (@atrupar) February 26, 2019The big lie the Majority Leader tells is to equate what happened in North Carolina with voter fraud.
That’s because what Dowless did was not voter fraud—it was election fraud and voters had nothing to do with it.